# .gitignore
# ----------
# This file tells Git which files and folders to ignore and never
# track or upload to GitHub. Any file or folder listed here will
# be invisible to Git even if it exists on your local machine.
#
# We mainly use this for three reasons:
# 1. Datasets are too large for GitHub (100MB file limit) so all
#    CSV, XLSX, and JSON files are excluded
# 2. Trained model files (.pkl) can be several hundred MB so those
#    are excluded too
# 3. Auto-generated junk files like Python cache (__pycache__) and
#    Jupyter auto-saves (.ipynb_checkpoints) add noise to the repo
#
# IMPORTANT: if a teammate needs the datasets they should download
# them manually from the links in README.md and place them in
# data/raw/ themselves. Never try to commit a dataset to this repo.

# Datasets - too large for GitHub
data/raw/
data/processed/
*.csv
*.xlsx
*.json

# Trained models - also large
results/*.pkl

# Python cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Jupyter auto-saves
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# OS junk files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Any secret keys
.env
secrets.py

.virtual_documents/
anaconda_projects/